BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. That section 3737.834 of the Revised Code be 4
enacted to read as follows: 5
Sec. 3737.834. (A) The state fire marshal shall ensure 6
that the inspection, testing, and maintenance of fire hydrant 7
systems in the state are conducted in accordance with this 8
section, the rules adopted as part of the state fire code, and 9
the recommended standards by the national fire protection 10
association. 11
(B) The fire marshal shall require any person or entity 12
responsible for maintaining a fire hydrant system to 13
periodically test that system. Fire hydrant systems shall be 14
maintained in an operative condition at all times and shall be 15
repaired where defective. Additions, repairs, alterations, and 16
servicing shall comply with all approved standards. Records of 17

