(C) At minimum, the fire hydrant systems and the 22
associated service mains and water tanks shall be periodically 23
inspected, tested, and maintained at the following intervals: 24
(1) Fire hydrants of all types shall be inspected annually 25
and after each operation. A flow test and general maintenance 26
for the fire hydrant shall be conducted annually. 27
(2) Fire service main piping shall be inspected annually 28
and a flow test shall be conducted every five years. 29
(3) Fire service main piping strainers shall be inspected 30
and receive general maintenance care after each use. 31

